<DOC><DOCNO> AP900505-0002 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-05-90 0126EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Greece-Albania     05-05 0147</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Greece-Albania,0152</SECOND><HEAD>Greece Recalls Ambassador Over Incident at Embassy in Albania</HEAD><DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Greece recalled its ambassador fromAlbania after accusing that country's security officials ofpursuing an asylum seeker into the Greek embassy, beating him, anddragging him away.   Greek officials say armed Albanian security officials moved intoembassy in Tirana, the Albanian capital, on Sunday. They say theofficials beat the asylum seeker and took him away.   Ambassador Spyros Dokianos was recalled to Athens on Friday forconsultations, said government spokesman Vyron Polydoras.   Relations between the two neighboring Balkan countries have beentense since late last year. Greece says an ethnic Greek minority ismistreated in Albania, Europe's last hard-line Communist nation.   Albania has an ethnic Greek minority of about 250,000 in apopulation of more than 3 million. Religious worship is forbiddenand attempts to flee the country are punished severely.</TEXT></DOC>